\begin_layout Subsection
Modules
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\family typewriter
spi_demo:
 
\family default
Texas Instruments CCS project that demonstrates how to use SPI signals for simple UART communication.
 This module is co-opted and used for all parts of the lab when sending data to the OLED.
 Note this also includes usage for the MCU as both a master & slave:
 we leave just the code for master,
 since that is all that the MCU will be doing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\family typewriter
i2c_demo:
 
\family default
Texas Instruments CCS project that demonstrates how to use I2C signals for simple reading operations with the BMA222 accelerometer.
 Namely,
 using the UART terminal to print out the changing accelerometer axis values (x,
 y,
 and z) when the MCU is rotated in physical space.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\family typewriter
Adafruit SSD1351 Open Source Graphics Library:
 
\family default
Abridged from the Adafruit graphics library,
 provides an API to write commands (and their subsequent data) to the OLED,
 as well as turn it on.
 Includes various functions to draw complex shapes on the digital display.
 This library is used extensively in this lab & modified.
 More information on the modifications will be detailed.
\end_layout

